What the system does:

- Extracts skills from CVs, including experience and project sections
- Extracts structured job requirements from job descriptions using Mistral
- Captures company context such as company name, domain, business problem, and organization mission
- Compares CV skills against saved or newly uploaded job roles
- Shows exact matched and missing skills by category so users can clearly understand why they are or are not a fit
- Calculates weighted match scores with explainable category-wise breakdowns
- Lets admins configure scoring metrics, skill weights, skill aliases, and broad skill mappings through the UI
- Provides downloadable outputs, including extracted job-profile JSON, generated question sets as JSON/PDF, complete interview preparation reports as PDF, and adaptive interview reports as PDF
- Generates focused interview practice questions for a selected skill
- Supports company-context-aware interview generation
- Supports adaptive interview mode that moves between skills based on learner performance
- Evaluates interview answers through a hybrid scoring pipeline: structured rubrics, Python code execution, test-based checks, and RAG-grounded context, rather than relying solely on an LLM-generated score
- Provides live Python coding practice for coding-style interview questions
- Supports RAG-grounded question generation from uploaded learning material
- Allows admins to manage users, evaluation datasets, scoring configuration, and model settings

