RAG architecture:

For grounded interview generation and evaluation, the system supports verified learning material.

The RAG flow is:

Uploaded documents
↓
Stored under data/grounding/documents
↓
Chunked with LangChain RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter
↓
Embedded using HuggingFace sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2
↓
Stored in FAISS
↓
Retrieved using role, selected skill, and optional grounding query
↓
Passed as context to the LLM for grounded question generation or grounded answer evaluation

The system supports:

- use existing FAISS index
- recreate index
- update index
- document registry with file hashes
- chunk metadata
- vector database inspection through an admin learning UI

Interview scoring architecture:

The system does not simply ask the LLM for a final score.

It uses structured evaluation:

- The LLM generates or receives expected points and rubric criteria
- The backend validates the question and evaluation structure
- For common Python topics, deterministic templates can replace LLM-generated expected points
- For coding questions, Python test cases can be used
- For grounded questions, retrieved context is used as source of truth
- Final score is calculated from structured score breakdowns rather than blindly trusting a single LLM number

Evaluation work:

I also started building an evaluation layer for the system.

Currently, I am focusing on job-description extraction evaluation first, because if job extraction is weak, CV-job matching will also be misleading.

The evaluation setup now includes:

- structured JSON job-description datasets
- manually labeled expected job skills
- category-level evaluation for:
  - strongly required skills
  - required skills
  - preferred skills
  - tools and platforms
- precision, recall, and F1 scoring
- comparison against saved Mistral-extracted job profiles
- React admin UI to create new evaluation datasets

This helped reveal real gaps, such as extracted job profiles not always aligning with manually expected skill categories. That is useful because the system now has a feedback loop for improving prompts, normalization, taxonomy, and extraction quality.

Some technical choices:

- FastAPI for backend APIs
- React for the primary frontend
- Mistral for job extraction and interview generation/evaluation
