What I learned:

Building an LLM application is not only about calling a model.

The difficult parts are:

- designing the schema
- keeping outputs structured
- normalizing equivalent skills such as RAG and retrieval-augmented generation
- making scoring explainable
- adding deterministic checks where LLMs are too variable
- separating normal LLM generation from grounded RAG generation
- creating evaluation datasets so the system can actually improve (more challenging for interview generation and personalized learning profile)

Future enhancements I want to add:

